                            <comment id="12857834" author="cathodion" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 14:35:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about using &lt;a href=&quot;http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/ConcurrentHashMap.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://java.sun.com/j2se/1.5.0/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/ConcurrentHashMap.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Wouldn&apos;t that solve the issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12857837" author="fmeschbe" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 14:40:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, but I don&apos;t want to get Java 5 dependent with the Declarative Services implementation (yet).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12857840" author="fmeschbe" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2010 14:54:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed a fix in Rev. 934927 synchronizing access to the maps (and making local copy if appropriate)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12859694" author="pderop" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2010 07:27:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello Felix,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does your last commit fully resolve this issue ? &lt;br/&gt;
I ask this because the issue is still &quot;in progress&quot; and I wonder if I can incorporate your fix in our product now, or if I should wait until the issue is fully resolved ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12859698" author="fmeschbe" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2010 07:36:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes the commit fixes the issue. Wanted to keep it open until I get a confirmation (which I failed to follow up on).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, this can be resolved fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12859702" author="pderop" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2010 07:46:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Felix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12898879" author="fmeschbe" created="Mon, 16 Aug 2010 12:11:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Apache Felix Declarative Services 1.6.0 has been released. The issues are now closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
